  "business_context": "Invoice records hold the formal billing demand. Each invoice represents one billing event — request payment of an amount, by a date, for specific line items. Invoices flow from Orders (or directly from won Opportunities in simpler models) and produce Payment records when customers pay. The accounting integration is the most-considered aspect — most CRM Invoice objects are mirrors of records that live authoritatively in an ERP / accounting system (QuickBooks, NetSuite, Sage, Xero), with sync logic keeping them aligned. Salesforce added a native Invoice object as part of Salesforce Billing / Revenue Cloud. EspoCRM has Invoice in Sales Pack. HubSpot added Invoices in 2024. Attio has no native Invoice. CiviCRM has invoicing tied to Contributions rather than as a separate entity. Bloomerang has no Invoice. Nonprofit deployments rarely use Invoices for donations (since donations are voluntary, not invoiced) but may use them for pledged-but-not-paid reminder workflows. When interviewing clients, surface \"Invoice\" by asking whether they bill customers from the CRM and whether the CRM needs to know payment status (versus delegating that entirely to an ERP / accounting system).",
  "catalog_id": "invoice",
  "common_synonyms": [
    "Bill",
    "Receivable",
    "Statement"
  ],
